  "doc_id": "42290",
  "text": "Indeed, a meta-analysis revealed that a specific chronomodulated chemotherapy protocol led to better treatment response and prolonged overall survival in men with colorectal cancer by 3.3 months [CITATION_1] . This result was however, not applicable to women underlying the need for gender and patient specific dosage timing protocols. A study to evaluate the advances of cisplatin-based chronotherapy in patients with advanced non-small cell lung cancer did not yield significant differences between the groups regarding the total response rate [CITATION_2] . Another study on the relapse risk for children with acute lymphoblastic leukemia, shows a dependency of time in terms of event-free survival outcome and favours evening treatment schedules [CITATION_3] .",
